From: "C.R. Sauls"
> First guess, brake fluid or grease on the brake shoes on the RIGHT side.
>
> Craig

No....brakes 'pull' to the side that works.  If the friction material does not
grab anything, it cannot slow it down. If the RIGHT side is contaminated, it
would pull left.


